# UX Template Rules

## DO NOT

- Edit files in `unpackaged/post_ux/` — fully regenerated by assembler
- Add `layoutAssignment` or `applicationVisibilities` to `force-app/` profiles
- Add `EmailTemplatePage` flexipages to `templates/flexipages/`
- Recreate object `.object-meta.xml` with `actionOverrides` in `force-app/`
- Duplicate a standalone flexipage across multiple feature dirs

## Never Edit `unpackaged/post_ux/`
That directory is fully regenerated on every `assemble_and_deploy_ux` run. Edit source templates here instead.

## Flexipages
- **Base**: `templates/flexipages/base/` — 25 base flexipages
- **Standalone overrides**: `templates/flexipages/standalone/{feature}/` — complete page replacements
- **Patches**: `templates/flexipages/patches/{feature}/` — YAML semantic patches applied on top of standalones/base
- One canonical standalone per page — don't duplicate across features
- Priority order (last wins): payments → billing → qb → tso → constraints → ramps → collections → utils → docgen → approvals
- `EmailTemplatePage` flexipages cannot deploy via Metadata API — do NOT add them here

## Layouts
- **Base**: `templates/layouts/base/` — always assembled
- **Feature**: `templates/layouts/{feature}/` — added when feature flag is true
- Last write wins for same-named layout

## Profiles
- `force-app` profile is stripped to classAccesses only — never add layoutAssignment or applicationVisibilities there
- Full profiles live in `templates/profiles/base/`
- Feature patches in `templates/profiles/patches/{feature}/`

## Objects
- Compact layouts and list views in `templates/objects/{feature}/`
- Object `.object-meta.xml` with actionOverrides/compactLayoutAssignment in `templates/objects/base/`
- These are forceignored in `force-app/` — don't recreate them there

## Applications
- `RLM_Revenue_Cloud` variants: `tso > qb > base` priority
- Feature-conditional actionOverrides via `templates/applications/patches/{feature}/`
